from flask import Flask, send_from_directory
import os

app = Flask(__name__)

# Define paths to your repositories
REPO_PATHS = {
    'satellite-baas': '/path/to/satellite-baas.github.io',
}

@app.route('/')
def index():
    return """
    <html>
        <head><title>Repository Server</title></head>
        <body>
            <h1>Repository Content Server</h1>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="/satellite-baas">Satellite BaaS</a></li>
            </ul>
        </body>
    </html>
    """

@app.route('/satellite-baas/<path:filename>')
def serve_satellite_baas(filename):
    return send_from_directory(REPO_PATHS['satellite-baas'], filename)

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run(host='0.0.0.0', port=8080)
```

This server:
1. Serves the satellite-baas repository under `/satellite-baas/`
2. Includes a simple index page with links to the repositories
3. Uses Flask's `send_from_directory` for secure file serving
4. Listens on port 8080

To use this:
1. Update the `REPO_PATHS` dictionary with correct paths
2. Run with `python server.py`
3. Access via `http://localhost:8080`

